Filament DEG GO CC (Cellular component) Analysis

deg_fila <- read_csv("filament_cell_DEGs_results.csv")
filament_genes <- deg_fila$feature_name[deg_fila$expression_category == "Highly expressed in filaments"]
cell_genes <- deg_fila$feature_name[deg_fila$expression_category == "Highly expressed in cells"]
cat("Filament genes:", length(filament_genes),
    "\nCell genes:", length(cell_genes), "\n")
## Filament genes: 738 
## Cell genes: 1572
annotated_genes <- getBM(
  attributes = c("hgnc_symbol", "description", "gene_biotype", "go_id", "name_1006"), 
  filters = "hgnc_symbol",
  values = filament_genes, 
  mart = ensembl
)
annotated_genes_grouped <- annotated_genes %>%
  group_by(hgnc_symbol, description, gene_biotype) %>%
  summarise(go_terms = paste(unique(name_1006), collapse="; "), .groups = "drop")

go_results_fila <- enrichGO(
  gene          = filament_genes,
  universe      = background_genes,
  keyType       = "SYMBOL",
  OrgDb         = org.Hs.eg.db,
  ont           = "CC",  # Cellular Component 
  pAdjustMethod = "BH",
  pvalueCutoff  = 0.05,
  qvalueCutoff  = 0.2
)
dotplot(
  go_results_fila,
  showCategory = 10,
  title        = "Top 10 GO Terms, Filament CC",
  font.size    = 15
) +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank()
  )

Filament UTR Analysis

all_genes <- unique(c(filament_genes, cell_genes))
mart <- useMart("ensembl", dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl")
structure_attrs <- c(
  "ensembl_transcript_id",
  "strand",
  "5_utr_start",
  "5_utr_end",
  "3_utr_start",
  "3_utr_end"
)

structure_data <- getBM(
  attributes = structure_attrs,
  filters    = "hgnc_symbol",
  values     = all_genes,
  mart       = mart
)
feature_attrs <- c(
  "ensembl_transcript_id",
  "hgnc_symbol",
  "transcript_is_canonical"
)

feature_data <- getBM(
  attributes = feature_attrs,
  filters    = "hgnc_symbol",
  values     = all_genes,
  mart       = mart
)
merged_data <- left_join(structure_data, feature_data, by = "ensembl_transcript_id")
merged_data_canonical <- merged_data %>%
  filter(transcript_is_canonical == 1)

summarized_utr <- merged_data_canonical %>%
  mutate(
    partial_5_utr_length = ifelse(
      !is.na(`5_utr_start`) & !is.na(`5_utr_end`),
      abs(`5_utr_end` - `5_utr_start`) + 1,
      0
    ),
    partial_3_utr_length = ifelse(
      !is.na(`3_utr_start`) & !is.na(`3_utr_end`),
      abs(`3_utr_end` - `3_utr_start`) + 1,
      0
    )
  ) %>%
  group_by(ensembl_transcript_id, hgnc_symbol) %>%
  summarize(
    five_utr_length  = sum(partial_5_utr_length),
    three_utr_length = sum(partial_3_utr_length),
    .groups          = "drop"
  )

summarized_utr_labeled <- summarized_utr %>%
  mutate(
    gene_group = case_when(
      hgnc_symbol %in% filament_genes ~ "filament",
      hgnc_symbol %in% cell_genes     ~ "cell",
      TRUE                               ~ NA_character_
    )
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(gene_group))

summarized_utr_labeled %>%
  group_by(gene_group) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_5utr   = mean(five_utr_length, na.rm = TRUE),
    median_5utr = median(five_utr_length, na.rm = TRUE),
    mean_3utr   = mean(three_utr_length, na.rm = TRUE),
    median_3utr = median(three_utr_length, na.rm = TRUE),
    n           = n()
  )
## # A tibble: 2 × 6
##   gene_group mean_5utr median_5utr mean_3utr median_3utr     n
##   <chr>          <dbl>       <dbl>     <dbl>       <dbl> <int>
## 1 cell            229.         166     1830.        1176  1766
## 2 filament        201.         142     1920.        1164   817
t.test(five_utr_length ~ gene_group, data = summarized_utr_labeled)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  five_utr_length by gene_group
## t = 3.3439, df = 1872.2, p-value = 0.0008424
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group cell and group filament is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  11.49030 44.08704
## sample estimates:
##     mean in group cell mean in group filament 
##               228.8584               201.0698
t.test(three_utr_length ~ gene_group, data = summarized_utr_labeled)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  three_utr_length by gene_group
## t = -0.948, df = 1513.2, p-value = 0.3433
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group cell and group filament is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -278.68718   97.08004
## sample estimates:
##     mean in group cell mean in group filament 
##               1829.531               1920.334
wilcox.test(five_utr_length ~ gene_group, data = summarized_utr_labeled)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  five_utr_length by gene_group
## W = 769924, p-value = 0.005918
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
wilcox.test(three_utr_length ~ gene_group, data = summarized_utr_labeled)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  three_utr_length by gene_group
## W = 714310, p-value = 0.687
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
summarized_utr_labeled$gene_group <- factor(
  summarized_utr_labeled$gene_group,
  levels = c("filament", "cell"),
  labels = c("Filament", "Cell")
)

df_long <- summarized_utr_labeled %>%
  select(hgnc_symbol, gene_group, five_utr_length, three_utr_length) %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(five_utr_length, three_utr_length),
    names_to = "utr_type",
    values_to = "utr_length"
  )

utr_labeller <- as_labeller(c(
  five_utr_length = "5' UTR length",
  three_utr_length = "3' UTR length"
))

p5 <- wilcox.test(five_utr_length  ~ gene_group,
                  data = summarized_utr_labeled)$p.value
p3 <- wilcox.test(three_utr_length ~ gene_group,
                  data = summarized_utr_labeled)$p.value

annot <- tibble::tibble(
  utr_type = c("five_utr_length", "three_utr_length"),
  x        = 1.5,
  label    = c(
    paste0("p = ", signif(p5, 3), if (p5 < 0.05) " *" else ""),
    paste0("p = ", signif(p3, 3), if (p3 < 0.05) " *" else "")
  )
)

max_info <- df_long %>%
  group_by(utr_type) %>%
  summarize(max_val = max(utr_length, na.rm = TRUE))

annot2 <- annot %>%
  left_join(max_info, by = "utr_type") %>%
  transmute(
    utr_type,
    xstart = x - 0.4,
    xend   = x + 0.4,
    y_bar  = max_val * 1.05,
    y_text = max_val * 1.10,
    h      = max_val * 0.02,
    label
  )

ggplot(df_long, aes(x = gene_group, y = utr_length, fill = gene_group)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.2, alpha = 0.5) +
  facet_wrap(~ utr_type, scales = "free", labeller = utr_labeller) +
  scale_fill_discrete(
    name   = "Gene Group",
    labels = c("Filament enriched genes", "Cell body enriched genes")
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "5′ vs. 3′ UTR Lengths in Filament vs. Cell Genes",
    x     = "Gene Group",
    y     = "UTR Length (bp)"
  ) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x      = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1)
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0.02, 0.15))) +
  geom_text(
    data      = annot2,
    aes(x = (xstart + xend)/2, y = y_text, label = label),
    inherit.aes = FALSE,
    size      = 5,
    vjust     = 0
  ) +
  geom_segment(
    data      = annot2,
    aes(x = xstart, xend = xend, y = y_bar, yend = y_bar),
    inherit.aes = FALSE,
    size      = 0.8
  ) +
  geom_segment(
    data      = annot2,
    aes(x = xstart, xend = xstart,
        y = y_bar, yend = y_bar - h),
    inherit.aes = FALSE,
    size      = 0.8
  ) +
  geom_segment(
    data      = annot2,
    aes(x = xend,   xend = xend,
        y = y_bar, yend = y_bar - h),
    inherit.aes = FALSE,
    size      = 0.8
  )
